I can't pinpoint what exactly the problem is here, but the following code configuration is throwing the compiler for a loop. On my local machine, it's throwing a stack overflow, but on the playground, I can't tell whether it's crashing or just taking a *really* long time to compile. Here is the code:

```
class ItemArgs<T>
{
	constructor(
		public Array: any,
		public Index: any,
		public Item: any) {}
}


interface Array<T>
{
	List: { (args: ItemArgs<T>): void; }[];
}
```
